  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed the <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 5-6 min <span class=\"text-danger\">[7-9 min]</span> or until the squash is fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min, or until starting to soften</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong>, 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has been absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> soy sauce </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>– this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> red Thai curry paste </strong>to the pan with the<strong> chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> ground paprika</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
